#define RespondBlackAdam ["Does that creature truly believe it can command us?","Ignore him, Adam. Some people are just looking for a reason to break things.","Such primitive roars. It reminds me of the beasts I fought in the deserts of Kahndaq.","He’s not a beast, he’s a threat. Let’s make sure he doesn't hurt anyone.","Do you hear that noise? It sounds like a child demanding attention.","It’s a dangerous child, Adam. Keep your guard up.","His strength is undeniable, yet his technique is non-existent.","Doesn't matter how he fights, he's destroying everything around him. Let's move.","My patience has reached its limit. Shall we put him in the dirt?","Only if he refuses to leave. Let's try to contain him first.","A wrestling match? He mocks the concept of combat.","He mocks everything. Let's see if he can handle the real thing.","Even a monster should know when he is outclassed.","He’s too angry to care. Stay alert; he’s faster than he looks.","I find his posturing tedious.","It's annoying, but we have to shut it down. Ready?"]

